<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America and Merrill Lynch&#39;s global sales and trading platform is at the center of the world&#39;s financial markets, providing liquidity, industry-leading insight and analytics, competitive pricing and execution across the debt, equity, commodity and foreign exchange markets.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
	
<p class="bac">
Associate Interns participate in a 10 week program based in Asia providing a unique opportunity and exposure to life in global markets.  In addition to learning opportunities there are formal and social opportunities to interact and network with senior business representatives.
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Placement</H3>
<p class="bac">
Depending on location, Associate Interns are either hired and placed directly with a specific team throughout the internship program or rotate through two desks.  Placement is determined during the hiring process matching the business needs and the interests/skills of the Associate Intern.  The various teams include (not all groups exist in all countries):
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Equities
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Cash Sales and Trading</li>
			<li>Equity Linked Product Sales, Trading and Structuring</li>
			<li>Global Markets Financing and Services</li>
			<li>Strategic Risk Trading</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Fixed Income, Currencies and Commodities
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Credit, Rates</li>
			<li>Currencies</li>
			<li>Foreign Exchange (FX)</li>
			<li>Local Currency Trading (LCT)</li>
			<li>Sales</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

<br>
<H3 class="bac">Responsibilities (vary with placement)</H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Assist on sales, trading, and hedging activities</li>
	<li>Assess market trends and provide quantitative data for clients</li>   
	<li>Perform market and quantitative research analysis   </li>
	<li>Help originate, structure, and model transactions</li>
	<li>Assist in structuring, pricing, and executing trades  </li> 
	<li>Assist in building knowledge of clients&#39; investment needs, assess market trends and macro economic themes, and help create appropriate solutions to meet clients&#39; needs </li>
	<li>Assist in providing quantitative data and succinct, comprehensive explanations of complex concepts to clients</li>
	<li>Work with teams to develop marketing presentations that create interest in fixed income  and Equity products and develop new business</li>
	<li>Assist in developing new products and bringing them to market</li>
	<li>Assist in educating clients about complex structures and technical products</li>
</ul>

